verbose_text: The chi squared test revealed that the ROR1 level is related to pathology grade (p = 0.001) and vital status (p = 0.017), and the univariate and multivariate analyses revealed that the ROR1 expression level (p = 0.021), with a HR of 2.024 and a 95% CI of 1.106-3.706, is an independent prognostic factor in patients with breast cancer.
